    <div class="space-y-6 dark:text-gray-300 text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        <strong>IMEI Checker</strong> is a simple, user-friendly web application that allows users to validate and retrieve information about their device's IMEI (International Mobile Equipment Identity) number.
      </p>

      <p>
        The project was developed as a frontend and backend integrated application using:
      </p>

      <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
        <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> Tailwind CSS</li>
        <li><strong>Templating:</strong> Nunjucks</li>
        <li><strong>Backend:</strong> Node.js + Express</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        We prioritize clean code, responsive design, and a smooth user experience. IMEI numbers are validated using the Luhn algorithm, and mock data is used to demonstrate device lookup.
      </p>

      <p>
        This project is for educational and demonstration purposes only. No real device data is stored or transmitted.
      </p>

      <p>
        Feel free to explore the project, contribute, or use it as inspiration for your own applications.
      </p>


